&lt;h1 id=&#34;ts-api-spec&#34;&gt;
  TS API Spec
  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#ts-api-spec&#34;&gt;
    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TS 1st api spec with superb DX&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/tsapispec.demo.gif&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      &lt;h4&gt;My Caption&lt;/h4&gt;
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Everything is autocompleted and type supported.
As soon as schema is satisfied error disappears.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;maximum code sharing between nodes (assuming JS/TS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;fully typed end to end (including errors)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;uniform error handling (do runtime validation in non prod everywhere)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;generates router and apiClient and router from same spec(SSOT/contract)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intended to: suboptimal code in industry/lag contract drift
Overlap: openApi codegen RPC etc
leverage: for js both backend and frontend ts first zero drift code sharing.
Eliminates gen step and stale specs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;how: parser types &lt;a href=&#34;http://djuleayo.com/posts/parser-types/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;http://djuleayo.com/posts/parser-types/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

